Name: Lee
Intro: Member of Gray Raven. Somewhat aloof in manner. Good at computers and machines, he is responsible for Gray Raven's hardware and technical issues.
MissionInfo: I'm back. Here is the data you need.

Name: Lucia
Intro: The leader of Gray Raven. Brave and selfless, she is ever at the frontline of the war against the Corrupted.

Name: Liv
Intro: A member of Gray Raven. As one of the newest support Constructs, she's the anchor of the team.
MissionInfo: I'm back. Everything seems new and fresh...

Name: Bianca
Intro: Leader of the Purifying Force, elegant yet cold, always performing her orders to perfection.

Name: Nanami
Intro: Fun-loving yet mysterious and elusive, her hobby is observing humans, with a practical joke or two mixed in.
MissionInfo: Nanami just made a huge discovery!

Name: Kamui
Intro: Member of Strike Hawk, an outstanding solo operator. He is friendly and helpful, but his carelessness always gets him into trouble.

Name: Karenina
Intro: Trained at the Cosmos Technicians Union and a member of the Engineering Force, the fiery Karenina solves problems by blowing them up. The Purifying Force finds this useful.
MissionInfo: I did better than Lucia, and you know it.

Name: Watanabe
Intro: Leader of the Forsaken, who chose to leave Babylonia to protect Oasis with his comrades who have been forgotten by the world.
MissionInfo: I hope you are satisfied with the results...

Name: Lucia
Intro: Lucia's signature frame. As graceful as it is powerful, its mere appearance on the battlefield inspires its allies, earning it the "Dawn" sobriquet.

Name: Liv
Intro: Liv has cut her hair as a statement of her strong will to return to the battlefield.
MissionInfo: I hope I did not let you down...

Name: Lee
Intro: The limits have been broken. Past and present intertwine. Lee dominates the battlefield with superior computing power.
MissionInfo: Did you think I could fail?

Name: Liv
Intro: Behind the strength of Liv's heart is a simple dream, and such purity is why this frame is so powerful.

Name: Kamui
Intro: The result of Kamui's control over the Tenebrion that he was imbued with. This frame is able to switch freely between the two battle forms.

Name: Karenina
Intro: Taking off her jacket and releasing the weapon restriction, Karenina is able to unleash the full force of her flaming wrath to burn away everything in her way.
MissionInfo: I might not go the next time if I don't get praised...

Name: Nanami
Intro: Nanami's enhanced model, equipped with IR-005 propulsion wheels, allowing her to speed across the battlefield at ease. "Hehe, you can only see Nanami's afterimages now."
MissionInfo: Nanami's always the first one back!

Name: Lucia
Intro: A mysterious enemy encountered by Gray Raven in City 015. Powerful yet mercurial.
MissionInfo: Leave it to other Constructs next time.

Name: Watanabe
Intro: A frame specially designed to control spacecraft. It was used by Watanabe when he served in the Task Force.
MissionInfo: The battle result is good enough.

Name: Ayla
Intro: An Archaeological Team member from the World Government Association of Art in Babylonia. The "new blood" of Babylonia. Loves art with a passion.
MissionInfo: It's given me a great inspiration!

Name: Bianca
Intro: An illegally modified frame born during the time when the Construct tech was not mature. It can cause charge separation to produce lightning as a means of attack. Specializes in long-distance sniping.
MissionInfo: Annihilating all enemies is my duty.

Name: Sophia
Intro: External support for Gray Raven, Sophia also functions as an envoy for the Akdilek Commercial Alliance. Born an orphan on the Eternal Engine, now the sharpest blade of its leader Jamilah.

Name: Chrome
Intro: The leader of the Strike Hawk. Capable of relaying important intel through a secure and stable channel. He values the flawless completion of missions, and also the safety of all his teammates.

Name: Lucia
Intro: Babylonia developed this latest frame specifically for Lucia based on Gray Raven's experience and the data collected from Alpha.
MissionInfo: Let's go. Victory will be ours.

Name: Vera
Intro: Leader of Cerberus, and the backbone of Babylonia's long-range connection field test team. Vera's extreme methods and belligerent, elusive demeanor have put her at the center of many a controversy.
MissionInfo: A M.I.N.D.-linking Commandant, huh... Try not to disappoint me.

Name: Camu
Intro: An Alternant that was once a repressed alter-ego in Kamui's M.I.N.D., Camu has been given his own unit by Babylonia, and now specializes in operations in and around heavily-Corrupted Dead Zones.
MissionInfo: So that's how it is... What a disgusting world this is.

Name: Rosetta
Intro: Leader of the original Forest Guard, Rosetta has been taken in by Babylonia, designated as a special unit, and redeployed onto the battlefield in a more humanoid form.

Name: Qu
Intro: A Transcendant and the last head of Kowloong. After the Battle of Kowloong, she has gone into hiding and continued with her ambition to achieve the Tabula Akasha.

Name: Changyu
Intro: Born in Kowloong and a former member of the theater. He has become a bodyguard on Asslam after many twists and turns.
MissionInfo: Heyas, here to help. Don't worry about paying me, old man Hassen's got it all sorted.

Name: Luna
Intro: As an agent of the Ascension-Network, this is her complete combat form, in which she can manipulate the Heteromer energy of the Punishing Virus and constructs to deliver attacks with a power that transcends all Ascendants.

Name: 2B
Intro: 2B is an all-purpose battle android from the automated YoRHa infantry. She is equipped with a multitude of blades for close-quarters combat and can attack from range using the POD support system.

Name: 9S
Intro: This unit's official title is Model S, Number 9. While this YoRHa member possesses offensive capabilities, he specializes in survey missions—and is particularly skilled at information gathering and hacking.

Name: A2
Intro: A YoRHa prototype that specializes in close-quarter combat. Though not presently in use, it was originally created to speed along the implementation of other official models such as 2B and 9S.

Name: Wanshi
Intro: As a Strike Hawk member, Wanshi always has a sleepy look. But once you get to know him better, you will realize he can be very trustworthy when things have gone bad.

Name: Selena
Intro: Formerly a member of the Archaeological Team, Selena used to have a great singing voice. She was also known for her talent in art and her gentle yet resilient nature. After being rescued by an Ascendant following the space station and Red Tide incidents, she is now a Transcendant.

Name: Chrome
Intro: The second specialized frame of Babylonia's mid-term military Construct development plan. It has been adjusted and optimized based on Chrome's request.

Name: No. 21
Intro: Originally a Daedalus corporation experimental subject, and was recycled during a mission conducted by Kurono. Later, she was transferred to Babylonia's Task Force with Vera. She is gloomy and seemingly expressionless in appearance. However, she becomes exceptionally vicious and dangerous under extreme circumstances.

Name: Vera
Intro: A frame Vera used in the past. Designed as an advanced, decisive countermeasure against hostile Constructs, it was finally introduced as an official unit not long ago. Its weapon is a specially forged banner spear.

Name: Roland
Intro: Originally an actor of the Golden Age, Roland often appears to be cheerful and unpredictable, but he has an earnest nature.

Name: Liv
Intro: A member of the Gray Raven, who was originally a member of the Star of Life. Polite, kind, and considerate. Looks vulnerable but is able to handle extreme stress.

Name: Selena
Intro: Selena's backup frame. Made with the support of an artist from WGAA, it is free-spirited and lively like its namesake, but the sentiments it embodies are earnest and solemn.

Name: Pulao
Intro: The frame of Pulao, one of the Dragon Children, is not made from conventional components but has been carefully adapted to fit her M.I.N.D., allowing her to make the most of her unusually strong powers.

Name: Nanami
Intro: A frame Nanami made for herself. It is extremely lightweight, but both the technology inside it and its strength have reached a level that is far beyond the level of the human technology nowadays.

Name: Haicma
Intro: A mechanoid from the Church of Machina that roams Earth in search of the Sagemachina. Compared with other mechanoids, she seems to have other reasons for pursuing this "Sage".

Name: Karenina
Intro: A frame Karenina developed for the low-gravity environment on the Moon. The core power system is equipped with a cutting-edge miniaturized gravitation device, allowing for short-term air mobility.
MissionInfo: I won't go next time if you don't praise me.

Name: Noan
Intro: The frame "he" created in order to save Noan. It weighed only 41.3 kg at first. A lot of deteriorated parts were used to restrict the movement of the user. Babylonia remodeled it to ensure everything could run smoothly.

Name: Bianca
Intro: A new specialized frame devised by Kurono based on thorough research into the tissue of the Hetero-Hive Mother. It is equipped with the Phantom Tracer, which can decipher certain information left by the Punishing Virus.

Name: Bambinata
Intro: A frame that has undergone a series of optimizations and modifications based on the Construct Kurono created during the early years. She has become an important member of the Egret squad since she started serving with the Task Force.

Name: Lee
Intro: A new specialized frame created using the information from the Heteromer Shard and the research materials of the Inver-Device. This creation boasts a certain level of expertise in deciphering the Punishing Language.

Name: Ayla
Intro: A new frame developed by Ayla as a chief developer. With state-of-the-art technical support from the WGAA, it maintains Ayla's signature style while ensuring its battle performance does not pale even beside combat-specialized frames.

Name: Lucia
Intro: Having experienced Ascension-Network's fluctuations, she walks the earth in a new form. Her changes are unknown, but her enhanced power is undeniable.

Name: Hanying
Intro: A mechanoid from Kowloong now waking up from her long sleep in the Church of Machina. Perfectly showcasing the fruit of Kowloong's machine technology through her appearance that extremely resembles a human being, she is still moving around as a mechanoid.

Name: No. 21
Intro: A new frame designed by Kurono with supervision from the Science Council. Customized to stabilize No. 21's M.I.N.D., it grants a massive increase in battle power while providing M.I.N.D. stability.

Name: Noctis
Intro: One of the Cerberus members. He was forced to leave the Purifying Force due to a mysterious conspiracy, but has now become a sharp fang of the three-headed hound.

Name: Alisa
Intro: Equipped with a special Aurora Squadron-made biological weapon—her armor "sister"—that is capable of M.I.N.D. connection, Echo is now traveling on the boundless earth in the pursuit of true justice.

Name: Lamia
Intro: Lamia's new frame designed by Luna with the Ascendant abilities. Enhanced based on Lamia's old frame, it is capable of switching freely between the human form and the mermaid form. Although Lamia whispered that she wanted a 170cm height, her human form height was only designed to be 169cm.

Name: BLACK★ROCK SHOOTER
Intro: A mysterious girl with a blue flame in her left eye and a giant cannon, who has traveled countless worlds.

Name: Watanabe
Intro: A frame independently developed by the Forsaken for tough battles with a brand-new design of the M.I.N.D. carrier module.

Name: Qu
Intro: A frame reforged by Tabula Akasha through life and death even with the Transcendant's Punishing Virus removed. Its principle and structure remain unknown.

Name: Teddy
Intro: Vice-captain of the Engineering Force. Since she is a programming expert, the core configurations of her frame are geared more toward a technician. However, this doesn't mean that she's not capable of combat—her stage is far beyond the battlefield in the physical world.

Name: Luna
Intro: Once an agent of the Ascension-Network, she now seeks to resist, guide, and control the entire Ascension-Network to create an ideal paradise after the Agent Zero incident.

Name: Bridget
Intro: A balanced duel-purpose frame capable of both attack and defense that the Science Council specially designed for the Support Force. It carries many special parts with part of its features adjusted accordingly.

Name: Hanying
Intro: Originally a female mechanoid in Kowloong, Hanying was kind and had her self-awakening through interactions with Pulao. Involved in an assassination, she was adopted by the Church of Machina and became a member of it with the seat of 'The Hanged Man.'

Name: Wanshi
Intro: This Tank frame is equipped with an advanced auto-aiming system while retaining some medical devices that are usually exclusive to Support frames. After retrieving all of his memory data, Wanshi has grown into a more complete version of himself. Though the long dream has yet to end, his path forward has already become clear.

Name: Lucia
Intro: Developed based on years of research of the Science Council, Pyroath is a new specialized frame carrying the Omega Core with efficient air combat capability. Through countless moments with Gray Raven, Lucia has found her purpose. Now, she's determined and calm just like the fire that forever burns on the frame.

Name: Yata
Intro: Following the style of the Yata human era, this unit is specifically designed for extended combat operations. Equipped with high-performance plasma armatures in its arm structure and rear-mounted mechanical arms, it can unleash devastating kinetic energy in an instant.

Name: Nanami
Intro: Designed by Nanami herself, this frame features a deep-space specialized protective coating, allowing her to barely withstand the corrosive surface environment of the Red Tide while also possessing exceptional interstellar navigation capabilities.

Name: Ishmael
Intro: Along with the rise and fall of countless civilizations, this is where Ishmael's choices intersect. This frame was born from a cosmos beyond time with materials beyond human comprehension, as enigmatic as the will of the Observer that operates within.

Name: Lilith
Intro: The convergence of Las Prados's wealth and Project Winter's technologies coalesced into this frame. Its eerie quality emanates not merely from the Ascension-Network's favor but more profoundly from the ambitions and desires deep inside her M.I.N.D., along with secrets buried in history's obscured chapters.

Name: Selena
Intro: A specialized frame co-developed by the Science Council and the World Government Association of Art with improved stability of M.I.N.D. to deal with Transcendants. The adaptee can use it with a suppression device to perform combat skills of multiple parts playing simultaneously.

Name: Jetavie
Intro: Say goodbye to the warm cradle and confront the painful awakening—she has traversed infinite loops to enter the real world with the full might of the matrix.

Name: Vera
Intro: A test frame developed by Kurono. It failed the berserk test after activation and was abandoned during a mission. Years later, Vera reactivated the frame, seized its control after fierce combats and chaos, and named it "Geiravor".

Name: Vergil
Intro: A legendary devil swordsman who masters lightning-fast quick-draw techniques. The elder twin of Dante.

Name: Dante
Intro: The boss of Devil May Cry, and the most powerful devil hunter alive. Revered for his legendary strength.

Name: Bianca
Intro: This is a new specialized frame developed by the Science Council, based on further validation of the Phantom Tracer. It can disrupt Punishing information to some extent, effectively weakening its influence.

Name: Discord
Intro: A new frame designed by Babylonia. Compared to Kurono's older model, its M.I.N.D. is less stable, with output levels prone to wide fluctuations.

Name: Veronica
Intro: A former member of the Church of Machina, who left the organization for various reasons and now operates independently. Prefers expressing herself through force rather than words.

Name: Liv
Intro: Developed by the Science Council, this new frame integrates data from the Golden Age's Phylotree of Ousia project into the M.I.N.D. Its success marks the dawn of a new era.
